{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nInit-time `_migrate_*`/`_ensure_*` steps run only at init/re-init, so config fixes never\nreach already-existing stores. A first-class idempotent ensure-registry generalizes them\n(School B desired-state) so every non-hot entry point converges an existing install.\n\n## What\nCreate `src/rebar/_store/ensures.py`: a registry of ensure units, each `{stable id,\ncheck-then-act callable}` that no-ops when converged and returns a typed result\n(`ok`/`changed`/`failed`). `run_ensures()` runs ALL units unconditionally under the tracker\nwrite lock, catches a raising unit (skip-and-continue â†’ `failed`), returns the per-unit result\nlist, and writes the COMPLETE current applied-id set to `.ensure-applied` (WS1 owns this file:\ngit-ignored, atomic temp+rename, a JSON array of id strings; absent/garbage â†’ empty set â€” a\nfull-set write, not an incremental append, so there is no read-modify-write race).\n\nMigrate exactly the 5 re-init idempotent steps (init.py:204-213): `env-id`, `gc-config`,\n`merge-ours driver`, `gitattributes` (COMMIT), `gitignore` (COMMIT). BOTH commit-producing\nunits (gitattributes AND gitignore â€” not just gitattributes) must tree-check before\ncommitting. The fresh-init-only bootstrap (`_commit_precommit`, `_gen_local_files`,\n`_exclude_scratch_in_tracker`, `_ensure_branch_user_config`) are NOT ensures and stay in the\nfresh-init path. Wire `init_core` to call `run_ensures()` and REMOVE the old hand-listed calls\n(no double-execution); confirm the 5 helpers have no other callers. init_core logs any\n`failed` units (warning) and NEVER aborts on an ensure failure.\n\n## Scope\nIn: `ensures.py`, registry + 5 migrated check-then-act units, typed result + partial-failure\ncontract, `run_ensures()` under the write lock, `.ensure-applied` format+write, init wiring\n(replace + remove old calls). Out: the pending-hint + `.ensure-hinted` (WS2), fsck/server\nwiring (WS3), docs (WS4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `ensures.py` holds a registry of units, each with a stable id + check-then-act callable returning a typed `ok`/`changed`/`failed` result; `run_ensures()` aggregates them and runs under the tracker write lock\n- [ ] All 5 re-init steps migrated; BOTH gitattributes and gitignore tree-check before committing; a second `run_ensures()` on a converged store makes zero changes and zero git commits (proven by a git-log assertion)\n- [ ] `init_core` calls `run_ensures()` AND the old hand-listed `_migrate_*`/`_ensure_*`/`_commit_*` calls are removed from it (no double-execution); the 5 helpers are confirmed to have no other callers\n- [ ] Partial-failure contract: a unit that raises is caught (skip-and-continue), recorded `failed`, excluded from `.ensure-applied`; init_core logs failures and never aborts\n- [ ] `.ensure-applied` is written atomically as a JSON array of the complete applied-id set; absent/garbage degrades to empty set without crashing\n- [ ] Fresh-init bootstrap steps (_commit_precommit/_gen_local_files/_exclude_scratch/_ensure_branch_user_config) remain in the fresh-init path and are NOT in the registry"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783571776835573001,"uuid":"ff60faaa-a551-4d9c-8ac6-437d1f7d763d"}